content: Techzac recommended  This app was listed #1 by Techzac website in 04/2016. 4stars, because I can't troubleshoot the sensitivity of the MagRes sensor. It alerts to any WiFi area that I have been in, which is every normal household now. If it could detect specific waste sounds from capaciters in recording devices, that might be different. Or, show the active wave forms of known frequencies. Or  detect RF signals rather than all MagRes. If there is a radio station finder based on area signals, that may be a better detector for rule-out discovery. The Ifra-red cam mode is not a true infra-red camera, it just filters the visials with a green multiplier, as far as I can tell. If this app helps you stop worrying and redduces info overload, then go for it! Otherwise, take it with a grain of salt.
replyContent: @Frequency detection - It is only possible if frequecy detector hardware connected to Android. Radio station like AM & FM have specific range of frequencies while Wifi works on specific range. Thats why its still not implemented.We are working on those options. @IR- your phone camera detects IR. See remote control head through camera.not just fancy
